{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0115zPmuSLmxQV579hcZ8cTN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the existing cluster:\n- Uses ES 7.17.9 without TLS\n- Has PVCs (data persisted)\n- The `es-http` service points to it (app: es-cluster)\n- Currently accessible via HTTP at port 9200\n\nI need to:\n1. Generate TLS certificates and create the `es-http-tls` secret\n2. Create the `elastic-password` secret  \n3. Delete the old StatefulSet (es-cluster)\n4. Create a new ConfigMap with proper ES 8.11.1 config (security + TLS)\n5. Create a headless service for node discovery\n6. Update the `es-http` service to point to the new StatefulSet\n7. Deploy the new StatefulSet with ES 8.11.1\n\nFor naming, I'll use `es` for the StatefulSet (creating pods `es-0`, `es-1`, `es-2`), `es-headless` for the discovery service, and keep `es-http` for the existing HTTP service but update its selector to match the new deployment.\n\nMy plan is to delete the old `es-cluster` StatefulSet, headless service, and ConfigMap, then create new versions with the updated configuration and ES 8.11.1 image. I'll keep the `es-http` service and just update its selector. Since ES 8 uses a different data format than ES 7, I don't need to worry about preserving the old PVCs—I can let the new StatefulSet create fresh volumes.\n\nNow I need to generate self-signed TLS certificates with the proper Subject Alternative Names for the Elasticsearch service endpoints.\n\nWriting cert generation script...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2077,"cache_read_input_tokens":40394,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2077},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a2d1657c-f337-44f6-8b43-4453e315faa8","uuid":"7256b9dc-8b6f-4fe9-a404-4e029ed373e4","request_id":"req_011CcMpoHeuCyq39dNyhKoFH"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0115zPmuSLmxQV579hcZ8cTN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The existing cluster runs ES 7.17.9 over plain HTTP — I need to tear it down and redeploy with ES 8.11.1 + TLS. Let me generate TLS certs, create secrets, and build the new deployment."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2077,"cache_read_input_tokens":40394,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2077},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a2d1657c-f337-44f6-8b43-4453e315faa8","uuid":"2d5dad39-0e93-4591-ad93-a5417954c520","request_id":"req_011CcMpoHeuCyq39dNyhKoFH"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0115zPmuSLmxQV579hcZ8cTN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01WFCBTkFPeh8t4ZvK6re6bK","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd /tmp && mkdir -p es-certs && cd es-certs\n\n# Generate CA key and cert\nopenssl genrsa -out ca.key 2048 2>/dev/null\nopenssl req -new -x509 -days 3650 -key ca.key -out ca.crt \\\n  -subj \"/CN=es-ca/O=elasticsearch\" 2>/dev/null\n\n# Create server cert with SANs for all ES endpoints\ncat > san.cnf << 'EOF'\n[req]\nreq_extensions = v3_req\ndistinguished_name = req_distinguished_name\n[req_distinguished_name]\n[v3_req]\nsubjectAltName = @alt_names\n[alt_names]\nDNS.1 = localhost\nDNS.2 = es-http\nDNS.3 = es-http.elasticsearch\nDNS.4 = es-http.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\nDNS.5 = *.es-headless.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\nIP.1 = 127.0.0.1\nEOF\n\nopenssl genrsa -out tls.key 2048 2>/dev/null\nopenssl req -new -key tls.key -out tls.csr \\\n  -subj \"/CN=elasticsearch/O=elasticsearch\" \\\n  -config san.cnf 2>/dev/null\nopenssl x509 -req -days 3650 -in tls.csr -CA ca.crt -CAkey ca.key \\\n  -CAcreateserial -out tls.crt -extensions v3_req -extfile san.cnf 2>/dev/null\n\necho \"CA cert:\"\nopenssl x509 -in ca.crt -noout -subject -issuer\necho \"Server cert SANs:\"\nopenssl x509 -in tls.crt -noout -text | grep -A5 \"Subject Alternative\"\necho \"Files: $(ls -la /tmp/es-certs/)\"","description":"Generate self-signed CA and server TLS certs with Elasticsearch SANs"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2077,"cache_read_input_tokens":40394,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2077},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a2d1657c-f337-44f6-8b43-4453e315faa8","uuid":"7b7670